result.markdown: --- title: "A normal post" date: "2022-07-30" jupyter: julia-1.11 --- ## Relearning Turing.jl This is a small julia post for relearning Turing.jl after a while and a lot of updates. ## Data We will use a dataset from a chapter on longitudinal data in the excellent online book on [Applied Modelling in Drug Development](https://opensource.nibr.com/bamdd/src/02g_longitudinal.html#data) written by statisticians from Novartis. The study data originates from a fictional longitudinal phase II study within dermatology studying a PASI score indicating severity of psoriasis for patients suffing from psoriasis. The study is an RCT with 50 subjects allocated to treatment and 50 subjects allocated to placebo. We will start of by modelling to study outcome at week 12. ::: {#6c2cbac2 .cell execution_count=2} ``` {.julia .cell-code} ## Load packages using Turing using CSV using DataFrames using TidierData using TidierPlots using CategoricalArrays # Load data from the parent folder adpasi = CSV.read(joinpath("..","..", "data", "longitudinal.csv"), DataFrame) # Name datasets and filter for PASI endpoint adpasi = @chain adpasi begin @filter(TRT01P in ["PBO", "TRT"]) end pasi_data = @chain adpasi begin @filter(PARAMCD == "PASITSCO") @arrange(AVISITN) @mutate(AVISITN1 = categorical(AVISITN)) end ``` ::: ## Overview ::: {#32df4d21 .cell execution_count=3} ``` {.julia .cell-code} ggplot(pasi_data, @aes(x = AVISITN, y = AVAL, dodge = TRT01P, color = TRT01P) ) + geom_violin() + theme_minimal() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` geom_violin data: inherits from plot x: inherits from plot y: inherits from plot ``` ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html} ``` ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=4} ```{=html} ``` ::: ::: ## Bayesian linear model We are going to posit the following model. $$ \begin{align} PASI_i &\sim \mathcal{N}(\beta^T X_i, \sigma^2)\\ \sigma^2 &\sim \mathcal{N}_+ (0, 10^2) \\ \beta_i &\sim \mathcal{N}(0, 10) \end{align} $$
